19 Sep 2008, 01:49 PM

Bradley Liddle

Technical Director Poliolite

My first visit to Ivory Coast was in 2001, we were invited by Ricardo to visit their factory as he had wanted us to send some equipment to them to be put into service. The factory is 120 miles east of Abidjan, which I visited in 2003 when I was asked to approach Sidel to purchase some of their equipment for the project which is still not completed. My interest in the market is for Polyolefins particularly Linear Low and it has been encouraging over the last year and a half, to see more of the Veroglass, Ocyglass projects being completed to Polyolefins in the last few months. Being a Polyolefin Rotomoulding Consultant to the three largest Plastic Rotomoulding plants in Ivory Coast during 2008, is a further interest which I had just not anticipated on visiting Africa.This is definately the place to be, especially for Polyolefin Rotomoulding.......Work never seems boring
